<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-24T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.35112 RP/2–2445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-24T14:00:00-03:00">February
                                    24, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 24—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>373. Fiore has submitted to Embassy list of 44 German firms intervened to
                            date. This figure comprises 19 principal companies and 25 subsidiaries.
                            List being forwarded by pouch.<note n="93" xml:id="d315fn93">Despatch
                                17,373, February 24, not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>He also advises that Perón<note n="94" xml:id="d315fn94">Juan D. Perón,
                                Vice President and Minister of War.</note> is exercising pressure on
                            him to go easy on the intervention of certain German firms because of
                            existing <pb facs="0462" n="448" xml:id="pg_448"/> army contracts with
                            them; Fiore claims he will not yield to this pressure.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>